s they can be backdated to either: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>6 April - if your claim is received by 5 May </li>\n  <li>1 month before your claim - if your claim is received after 5 May </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You might know your income is going to drop if, for example, you or your partner are being made redundant, leaving a job or taking a pay cut. </p>\n\n<p>The income levels for <a href=\"/working-tax-credit\" title=\"Working Tax Credit\">Working Tax Credit</a> and <a href=\"/child-tax-credit\" title=\"Child Tax Credit\">Child Tax Credit</a> are different. </p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/claim-tax-credits/joint-claims","slug":"joint-claims","order":3,"title":"Joint claims","body":"<p>You can apply for tax credits as a single person or as a couple (known as a &lsquo;joint claim&rsquo;). </p>\n\n<p>You must make a joint claim if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you’re married or in a civil partnership</li>\n  <li>you’re not permanently or legally separated </li>\n  <li>you live with your partner as though you’re married or in a civil partnership</li>\n  <li>you’re temporarily living away from your partner - eg to look after a relative</li>\n  <li>your partner lives with you in the UK but works abroad </li>\n  <li>you and your partner live abroad but work in the UK and don’t have children</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Exception</h2>\n\n<p>Claim as a single person if all the following apply: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you regularly travel to or from the UK for work</li>\n  <li>you don&rsquo;t live in the UK </li>\n  <li>you have no children </li>\n  <li>your partner doesn’t work in the UK (if you have one)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If you don’t make the right sort of application you must pay back any tax credits you’re not entitled to.</p>\n</div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/claim-tax-credits/backdate-a-claim","slug":"backdate-a-claim","order":4,"title":"Backdate a claim","body":"\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>When you make a claim y